            Hint: For <m>s(a,b) = (8,2)</m> we want integers <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> such that <m>a+b=8</m> and <m>a-b=2</m>.
            The second equation tells us <m>a = b+2</m>.
            Either guess from here or plug into the first equation to get <m>(b+2)+b=8</m>.
            Solve for <m>b</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Hint: For <m>s(a,b) = (2,1)</m> we want integers <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> such that <m>a+b=2</m> and <m>a-b=1</m>.
            The second equation tells us <m>a = b+1</m>.
            Plug into the first equation to get <m>(b+1)+b=2</m>.
            Solve for <m>b</m>.
          </p>
